? <br /><br />Anyway, wrt the aha152x driver: could you try the _newest_ pre-patch<br />(currently #4) to see if the aha152x driver works with my version of your fix<br />too? I've written the code to do it portably, but I obviously cannot test if<br />it actually works.. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
